@node hist "What has come before"
@toc "main"

@{u}History@{uu}

° 13-14th Feb :

    ° V1.0 First Aminet release.

° 18th Feb:

    ° V1.5 Now will delete original roms and dirs AFTER completing
      archiving. (Selectable)
    ° Still working on 'ROMs' dir bug...

° 19th Feb:

    ° V1.5 Fixing bugs in Progress Indicator, it doesn't complete
      it's journey and craps out in the end.  :-/
    ° Added code for deleting of archives, and some bugs.  I'm
      trying to remove it.  Will be fixed before release !

° 22nd Feb:

    ° V1.5 Fixed the delete dirs problem.  Now needs 'Delete' to be in
      the 'C' directory...
    ° Progress indicator seems to be fixed.  Still needs more tests.
    ° I have a possible solution to the 'ROMs' dir bug...  Coming soon.


° 26th Feb:

    ° V2.0 Fixed the 'roms' bug that has been bugging (pun intended)
      me for a few days.
    ° You may now archive the roms anywhere you like, including back
      to your original MAME directory.
    ° The program will ignore the following directories:

      ° cfg     : The config's directory.
      ° hi      : The highscore directory.
      ° samples : The directory where all the samples are kept.
      ° roms    : Where the archived roms are stored.

      And not archive their contents.

    ° Progress Indicator is definitely fixed, no more stack errors.


@endnode

@node auth "Who am I ?"
@toc "main"


A little info about myself:

I am a 26 year old over worked, underpaid bank teller.

I live in a fairly large city about 40km south west of Sydney, NSW,
Australia, called Campbelltown.  No, I don't recall the population
size, but driving from one side to the other takes about 45 minutes.

I started into Blitz Basic coding a little while ago (about 2 years
now), but have only in the last 6-8 months really started to do some
relatively decent coding.

Im a mega fan of emulators, of all shapes and sizes, and collect the
suckers, just to prove to people that, YES, the Amiga can do that
(anything the IBM compats) as well !  Currently I have over 180 megs
of emulators and related rom files for a multitude of emulators.

I have been asked by a number of people on my opinion of them
(emulators), and have spoken to some relatively famous people in the
Amiga circuit.

Well, thats me !  What do I intend on doing in the future.  I want to
get into C and C++ coding.  Mainly so I can move to programming PC's
in the future.  No I would not abandon the Amiga, heck I like the
machine too much, that and I have spent a fortune on this baby !!!

=)


/Rodney Norton 1998.


@endnode

